from the encyclopaedie van nederlandsch westindië  saba island as viewed from the north with mount scenerys peak in the clouds saba consists largely of the potentially active volcano mount scenery at  metres  ft the volcano is the highest point within the kingdom of the netherlands the vegetation of saba is mainly composed of woodland forest with ferns and damp soil and many mango trees visitors refer to sabas forests as the elfin forest because of its high altitude mist and mossy appearance a woodland reserve was created and named elfin forest reserve sabas lush plant and animal wildlife is diverse and is cared for by the saba conservation foundation there used to be forests of mountain mahogany trees until a hurricane in the s destroyed many of the trees which are freziera undulata in the family theaceae despite the common name these trees are not related to other mahogany species one species of true mahogany tree is found planted on the island at lower levels and that is the smallleaved mahogany swietenia mahagoni meliaceae the native mahogany trees are considered to be at risk of becoming extinct on saba  kilometres  mi southwest of saba is the edge of the saba bank a very large submerged atoll with especially rich biodiversity saba bank is the top of a sea mount and it is a prime fishing ground particularly for lobster a nongovernmental conservation organization saba conservation foundation helps protect the nature and culture of the island governanceedit sabas government house saba became a special municipality within the country of the netherlands after the dissolution of the netherlands antilles on  october  the head of the island is the island governor current held by jonathan g a johnson previous title holders include john hassell charles simmons edward beaks richard johnson moses leverock henry every wycliffe smith sydney sorton societyedit a typical saba view the population of saba the sabans consists of  people who come from all over the world sabas small size has led to a fairly small number of island families who can trace their last names back to around a halfdozen families this means that many last names are shared around the island the most numerous being hassell and johnson most families are an intermixing of dutch english scottish and african heritage the population is also descended from the irish who were exiled from that country after the accession of king charles i of england in  charles exiled these irish to the caribbean in an effort to quell rebellion after he had forcibly procured their lands for his scottish noble supporters historically saba was traded among the many european nations that fought for power in the region slaves were also imported to work on saba in recent years saba has become home to a large group of expatriates and around  immigrants who are either students or teachers at the saba university school of medicine languagesedit both english and dutch are spoken on the island and taught in schools and both languages are official despite the islands dutch affiliation english is the principal language spoken on the island and has been used in its school system since the th century english can therefore be used in communications of and to the government saba english a form of virgin islands creole english is the local vernacular education and healthedit saba is home to the saba university school of medicine which was established by american expatriates in coordination with the government of the netherlands the school adds over  residents when classes are in session and it is the prime educational attraction am edwards medical center is the major provider of healthcare for local residents samesex marriageedit in saba as in bonaire and sint eustatius marriage is open to same sex and opposite sex couples following the entering in force of a law enabling also samesex couples to marry on  october  the first samesex marriage was performed on saba on  december  between a dutch and a venezuelan man both residing in aruba where samesex marriage is not performed economyedit main article economy of saba since  the us dollar has been the official currency replacing the netherlands antillean guilder agriculture on saba is primarily livestock and vegetables especially potatoes saba lace also known as spanish work is actually drawn thread work and as of update it is still produced on the island tourismedit a playground on saba the tourism industry now contributes more to the islands economy than any other sector there are about  visitors each year saba has a number of inns hotels rental cottages and restaurants saba is known as the unspoiled queen of the caribbean saba is especially known for its ecotourism having exceptional scuba diving climbing and hiking the juancho e yrausquin airport offers flights to and from the nearby islands of st maarten and sint eustatius there is also a ferry service from st maarten the ferry boats dawn ii  the saba ferry and the edge both travel to saba three times a week in addition there are anchorages for private boats about  species of fish have been found in sabas waters a main draw for divers are the pinnacle dive sites where magma pushed through the sea floor to create underwater towers of volcanic rock that start at about  feet  m down and rise to about  feet  m beneath the surface the waters around saba were designated as the saba national marine park in  and are subject to government regulation to preserve the coral reefs and other marine life the saba conservation foundation has operated a hyperbaric chamber in case of diving emergencies since  transportedit a view of the village of windwardside taken from mount scenery there is one main road known as the road its construction was masterminded by josephus lambert hassell who despite the common opinion of dutch and swiss engineers believed that a road could be built he took a correspondence course in civil engineering and started building the road with a crew of locals in  after five years of work the first section of the road from fort bay to the bottom was completed it was not until  that the first motor vehicle arrived in  the road to windwardside and st johns was opened and in  the road was completed driving the road is considered to be a daunting task and the curves in windwardside are extremely difficult to negotiate driving is on the right hand side in citation needed saba residents built the juancho e yrausquin airport this metre  ft landing strip is reputed to be the shortest commercial runway in the world and is restricted only trained pilots flying small stol airliners such as the twin otter and the brittennorman islander may land there as well as helicopters consistent air service from sint maarten and sint eustatius is available through winair in  a pier was completed in fort bay to access the island travel is also provided by ferry services to and from sint maarten with the dawn ii and the edge of note are  steps carved from stone that reach from ladder bay to the settlement known as the bottom until the late th century everything that was brought to the island was carried up by hand using these steps the steps are now often used by tourists who wish to experience an intense climb culturaledit main article culture of saba sabas houses have a cottage look with red roofs the lifestyle is slow and oldfashioned with little nightlife even with the emergence of an ecotourism industry in the last few decades sabans are proud of their history of environmental conservation calling saba the unspoiled queen saban women continue to make two traditional island products saba lace and saba spice saba lace is handstitched lace which the islands women began making in the late th century and built into a thriving mailorder business with the united states saba spice is a rum drink brewed with a combination of spices as in other caribbean locations sabans throw an annual carnival sabas carnival takes place the last week in july and includes parades steel bands competitions and food another event held in the capital the bottom is saba day this is the national day of the island in which all offices schools and stores are closed the island celebrates its diversity and culture through various activities and parades the bottom holds host to a concert at the sports field where local and other caribbean artists come to perform sportsedit only a few sports are played on saba including volleyball the saba volleyball association is a member of norceca and basketball see alsoedit geography portal north america portal caribbean portal netherlands portal caribbean netherlands caribbean sea leeward islands referencesedit  a b population of dutch caribbean  january sex age saba statistics netherlands  january  retrieved  august    a b english can be used in relations with the government invoeringswet openbare lichamen bonaire sint eustatius en saba in dutch wettennl retrieved    the domain for the netherlands antilles has remained active after its dissolution the iso  alpha code bq was established for the entity bonaire sint eustatius saba iso  decoding table international organization for standardization retrieved   an internet cctld has however not been established by the iana and it is unknown if it will be opened for registration  mangold max duden – das aussprachewörterbuch in der duden in zwölf bänden band   auflage berlin dudenverlag mannheim  institut für deutsche sprache  seite   wet openbare lichamen bonaire sint eustatius en saba law on the public bodies of bonaire sint eustatius and saba dutch government in dutch retrieved  october    energy snapshot saint martin  sint maarten pdf national renewable energy laboratory retrieved  february    a b towards  sustainable energy on the caribbean island of saba low emission development strategies global partnership leds gp retrieved  march    preserving tradition on the island of women and lace brigham young university  retrieved    antillen opgeheven nos nieuws 